verses.text:
And when he had made a scourge of small cords, he drove them
all out of the temple, and the sheep, and the oxen; and poured out
the changers’ money, and overthrew the tables;

(But this spake he of the Spirit, which they that believe on
him should receive: for the Holy Ghost was not yet \add given\add*;
because that Jesus was not yet glorified.)

\wj  Father, glorify thy name.\wj* Then came there a voice
from heaven, \add saying\add*, I have both glorified \add it\add*,
and will glorify \add it\add* again.

\wj  Little children, yet a little while I am with you. Ye shall
seek me: and as I said unto the Jews, Whither I go, ye cannot come;
so now I say to you.\wj*

\wj  Whose soever sins ye remit, they are remitted unto them;
\+add and\+add* whose soever \+add sins\+add* ye retain, they are
retained.\wj*
